# Licensing

This repository mixes hardware design files and software. Different licenses apply
to different parts of the tree, as described below.

| Area | License | Full text |
|------|---------|-----------|
| KiCad projects, Gerbers, and PCB-related exports under `e-ink-PCBs/` | [CERN-OHL-W-2.0](https://opensource.org/license/cern-ohl-w) | [LICENSE-HARDWARE](LICENSE-HARDWARE) |
| Firmware under `e-ink_code/firmware/`, Python and shell scripts under `e-ink_code/scripts/`, configuration examples under `e-ink_code/config/`, and Markdown documentation at the repository root and under `e-ink_code/` | [MIT](https://opensource.org/license/mit) | [LICENSE-SOFTWARE](LICENSE-SOFTWARE) |

Unless a file or subdirectory states otherwise, the paths above determine which
license applies. Third-party components (for example KiCad library symbols,
footprints, or PlatformIO libraries) remain under their respective upstream
licenses.

SPDX identifiers used in this project:

- `CERN-OHL-W-2.0` for hardware design source in `e-ink-PCBs/`
- `MIT` for software and documentation described in the table above
